  "texts": [
    "For predicting time to DR progression, the system achieved concordance indexes of 0.754-0.846 and integrated Brier scores of 0.153-0.241 for all times up to 5 years.",
    "Furthermore, we validated the system in real-world cohorts of participants with diabetes.",
    "The integration with clinical workflow could potentially extend the mean screening interval from 12 months to 31.97 months, and the percentage of participants recommended to be screened at 1-5 years was 30.62%, 20.00%, 19.63%, 11.85% and 17.89%, respectively, while delayed detection of progression to vision-threatening DR was 0.18%.",
    "Altogether, the DeepDR Plus system could predict individualized risk and time to DR progression over 5 years, potentially allowing personalized screening intervals.",
    "DR is the most common microvascular complication of diabetes and the leading cause of preventable blindness in adults aged 20-74 years [1] [2] [3]."
